<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="159" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="159">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="159">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gil-Santana, Costa &amp; Marques" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Chryxus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chryxus bahianus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="159">Chryxus bahianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on a single male from the State of Bahia, northeastern Brazil. Unfortunately, the holotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. bahianus" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" rank="species" species="bahianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="159">C. bahianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was destroyed on the 2nd of September 2018, during the fire which destroyed most of the zoological collections, including the entire 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" rank="subOrder" subOrder="Heteroptera">Heteroptera</taxonomicName>
collection of the MNRJ (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1126/science.361.6406.960" author="Escobar, H" journalOrPublisher="Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" pagination=": 960" refId="B2" refString="Escobar, H, 2018. In a 'foretold tragedy,' fire consumes Brazil museum. Science 361 (6406): 960, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1126/science.361.6406.960" title="In a ' foretold tragedy, ' fire consumes Brazil museum." url="https://doi.org/10.1126/science.361.6406.960" volume="361" year="2018">Escobar 2018</bibRefCitation>
). However, images taken before the fire (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–9" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 9. Chryxus bahianus Gil-Santana, Costa &amp; Marques, 2007, male holotype, previously deposited in MNRJ 2 dorsal view 3 lateral view 4 labels 5 - 9 male genitalia 5 apex of pygophore and medial process of pygophore (pointed by arrows), posterior view 6, 7 paramere; laminar process pointed by an arrow 6 lateral view 7 inner surface 8, 9 phallus 8 lateral view 9 with endosoma and dorsal phallothecal sclerite set apart. Abbreviations: bpa basal plate arm, dps dorsal phallothecal sclerite, pd pedicel, pe process of endosoma, st struts. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (2, 3); 0.1 mm (5 - 9)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.79411.figures2-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/696161" pageId="0" pageNumber="159">2-4</figureCitation>
) in addition to the drawings presented in the original publication (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/S0101-81752007000100010" author="Gil-Santana, HR" journalOrPublisher="Revista Brasileira de Zoologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" pagination="77 - 83" refId="B4" refString="Gil-Santana, HR, Costa, LAA, Marques, OM, 2007. Sinopse dos Chryxinae (Hemiptera, Reduviidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia 24 (1): 77 - 83, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1590/S0101-81752007000100010" title="Sinopse dos Chryxinae (Hemiptera, Reduviidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/S0101-81752007000100010" volume="24" year="2007">Gil-Santana et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), are useful in providing a better knowledge of the holotype. Additionaly, a female (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 10–12" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 10 - 12. Chryxus bahianus Gil-Santana, Costa &amp; Marques, 2007, female specimen from Espirito Santo State, Brazil 10 dorsal view 11 ventral view 12 external genitalia, posterior view, schematic drawing, setation omitted. Abbreviations: sy IX / X syntergite IX / X, gc VIII gonocoxa VIII, gp VIII gonapophysis VIII, gp IX gonapophysis IX. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (10, 11); 0.1 mm (12)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.79411.figures10-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/696162" pageId="0" pageNumber="159">10-12</figureCitation>
) from the State of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Espírito">Espirito</normalizedToken>
Santo, a neighbouring state of Bahia, was included to this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
